This document describes the Microsoft Azure Log Analytics Nozzle for Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF).

## <a id='overview'></a>Overview

The Microsft Azure Log Analytics Nozzle for PCF receives logs and metrics from the Loggregator Firehose, filters and resolves the events, and then push the events to Azure Log Analytics via the HTTPS Data Collector API.

Azure Log Analytics collects data generated by resources in your cloud and on-premises environments, and provides analysis across multiple sources. Developers and operators can view their application logs and health metrics through the OMS (Operations Management Suite) portal or the Azure portal.

## <a id='features'></a>Key Features

Microsoft Azure Log Analytics Nozzle for PCF includes the following key features:

* Automated configuration for the Microsoft Azure Log Analytics Nozzle
* Resolved Cloud Foundry application metadata (for example, app name) in logs and metrics
* Filtering for different types of logs and metrics
* Additional logging for slow consumer alert
* Additional logging for statistics of received, sent and lost events of the nozzle
* Integration with Azure OMS Log Analytics, including view dashboards and alert rules for monitoring the health and workload of your PCF deployment

